### install aws cli in ubuntu

1. Install unzip first
sudo apt install unzip

2. Download the installation file
curl "https://awscli.amazonaws.com/awscli-exe-linux-x86_64.zip" -o "awscliv2.zip"

3. Unzip installer
unzip awscliv2.zip

4. Run the install program
sudo ./aws/install
 
5. Check aws path
which aws

6. Check aws version and confirm installation
aws --version

7. Configure aws by pasting the credentials in terminal (setting environment)
#from aws account

8. Check if the aws environment is set
aws s3 ls       ##if gives error on RequestTimeSkewed, shut down ubuntu first by wsl --shutdown in windows powershell terminal and restart to synchronize the time
